@startuml
!define AWSPuml https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
!include AWSPuml/AWSCommon.puml
!include AWSPuml/SecurityIdentityCompliance/SecurityHub.puml
!include AWSPuml/ApplicationIntegration/EventBridge.puml
!include AWSPuml/ApplicationIntegration/SimpleQueueService.puml
!include AWSPuml/ApplicationIntegration/StepFunctions.puml
!include AWSPuml/Compute/Lambda.puml
!include AWSPuml/ManagementGovernance/SystemsManager.puml
!include AWSPuml/ManagementGovernance/CloudWatch.puml
!include AWSPuml/SecurityIdentityCompliance/IdentityAccessManagementRole.puml

title Automated Security Response on AWS - Security Finding Remediation Flow

actor "Security\nAdministrator" as Admin
participant "Security Hub" as SecurityHub <<SecurityHub>>
participant "EventBridge\nRule" as EventBridge <<EventBridge>>
participant "SQS Queue" as SQS <<SimpleQueueService>>
participant "Orchestrator\n(Step Function)" as Orchestrator <<StepFunctions>>
participant "Parse Input\nLambda" as ParseLambda <<Lambda>>
participant "SSM Automation\nDocument" as SSMDoc <<SystemsManager>>
participant "Remediation\nLambda" as RemediationLambda <<Lambda>>
participant "IAM Role\n(Cross-Account)" as IAMRole <<IdentityAccessManagementRole>>
participant "Member Account\nResource" as MemberResource
participant "Update Finding\nLambda" as UpdateLambda <<Lambda>>
participant "CloudWatch\nLogs/Metrics" as CloudWatch <<CloudWatch>>
participant "Ticketing System\n(Jira/ServiceNow)" as Ticketing

== Security Finding Detection ==

SecurityHub -> SecurityHub: Detect security\nfinding from\nstandard check
activate SecurityHub

SecurityHub -> EventBridge: Publish finding event\n(CIS/FSBP/PCI/NIST)
deactivate SecurityHub
activate EventBridge

EventBridge -> SQS: Queue finding for\nthrottling
deactivate EventBridge
activate SQS

SQS -> Orchestrator: Trigger Step Function\nwith finding data
deactivate SQS
activate Orchestrator

== Finding Parsing and Validation ==

Orchestrator -> ParseLambda: Invoke parse_input.py\nwith Security Hub finding
activate ParseLambda

ParseLambda -> ParseLambda: Extract:\n- Control ID\n- Security Standard\n- Resource ARN\n- Account ID

ParseLambda -> ParseLambda: Validate finding\nand parameters

ParseLambda --> Orchestrator: Return parsed data\n(ControlId, Standard, Resource)
deactivate ParseLambda

== Remediation Selection and Execution ==

Orchestrator -> Orchestrator: Determine appropriate\nPlaybook based on\nSecurity Standard

Orchestrator -> Orchestrator: Map Control ID to\nSSM Automation Document

Orchestrator -> SSMDoc: Execute Automation\nDocument (Runbook)
activate SSMDoc

SSMDoc -> SSMDoc: Load remediation\nworkflow (YAML)

SSMDoc -> RemediationLambda: Execute remediation\nscript (aws:executeScript)
activate RemediationLambda

== Cross-Account Access and Remediation ==

RemediationLambda -> IAMRole: Assume role in\nMember Account
activate IAMRole

IAMRole --> RemediationLambda: Temporary credentials\n(least privilege)
deactivate IAMRole

RemediationLambda -> MemberResource: Apply remediation:\n- Update security group\n- Add tags\n- Modify configuration
activate MemberResource

MemberResource --> RemediationLambda: Remediation result
deactivate MemberResource

RemediationLambda -> CloudWatch: Log remediation\nactions and status
activate CloudWatch
deactivate CloudWatch

RemediationLambda --> SSMDoc: Return remediation\noutcome (success/failure)
deactivate RemediationLambda

SSMDoc --> Orchestrator: Automation execution\ncomplete
deactivate SSMDoc

== Finding Status Update ==

Orchestrator -> UpdateLambda: Update Security Hub\nfinding status
activate UpdateLambda

UpdateLambda -> SecurityHub: Mark finding as:\nRESOLVED/SUPPRESSED
activate SecurityHub

SecurityHub --> UpdateLambda: Update confirmation
deactivate SecurityHub

UpdateLambda --> Orchestrator: Status updated
deactivate UpdateLambda

== Metrics and Notifications ==

Orchestrator -> CloudWatch: Publish remediation\nmetrics (success/failure)
activate CloudWatch

CloudWatch -> CloudWatch: Update dashboard\nand trigger alarms\nif needed
deactivate CloudWatch

Orchestrator -> Ticketing: Create ticket\n(optional integration)
activate Ticketing

Ticketing --> Orchestrator: Ticket created
deactivate Ticketing

Orchestrator --> SQS: Remediation complete
deactivate Orchestrator

== Manual Remediation (Custom Action) ==

Admin -> SecurityHub: Select finding and\ninvoke Custom Action
activate SecurityHub

SecurityHub -> EventBridge: Trigger Custom Action\nevent
activate EventBridge

EventBridge -> Orchestrator: Initiate manual\nremediation workflow
activate Orchestrator

note right of Orchestrator
Manual remediation follows
same flow as automated
remediation from this point
end note

Orchestrator --> Admin: Remediation initiated
deactivate Orchestrator
deactivate EventBridge
deactivate SecurityHub

@enduml
